        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat: add skill allowlist merge config",
        "body": "Related #97567\n\n## What Problem This Solves\n\nResolves a problem where users who configure `agents.defaults.skills` or Telegram topic `skills` filters must restate the entire inherited skill allowlist whenever they only want to add or remove a small number of scoped skills.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\nAdds an opt-in `skillsMerge: { add, remove }` config shape for agent entries and Telegram topic configs while preserving existing `skills` replacement semantics. This PR treats `skillsMerge` as a concrete proposed contract for the maintainer/product decision called out on #97567: it composes only against a finite inherited filter, because the current runtime filter is allowlist-only and cannot represent \"all skills minus X\" safely.\n\nTelegram group/direct configs keep explicit `skills` replacement only; `skillsMerge` is intentionally limited to topics there, where a real inherited group/direct or `topics[\"*\"]` filter exists.\n\n## User Impact\n\nOperators can keep a shared baseline in `agents.defaults.skills`, then let an agent add project-specific skills or remove noisy baseline skills without copying the whole list. Telegram forum topics and DM topics can similarly adjust inherited skill filters without replacing the complete parent/default-topic list.\n\n## Evidence\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/agents/agent-scope.test.ts extensions/telegram/src/bot.create-telegram-bot.test.ts src/config/schema.test.ts` (3 shards passed: 58 config tests, 46 agent tests, 114 Telegram tests)\n- `node node_modules/oxfmt/bin/oxfmt --check --threads=1 src/config/types.telegram.ts src/config/zod-schema.providers-core.ts src/config/schema.test.ts extensions/telegram/src/group-config-helpers.ts extensions/telegram/src/bot.create-telegram-bot.test.ts src/config/bundled-channel-config-metadata.generated.ts`\n- `pnpm config:channels:check`\n- `git diff --check`\n- `pnpm tsgo:core && pnpm tsgo:extensions` (passed; local shell emitted the existing Node engine warning for v22.18.0 vs repo >=22.19.0)\n- `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode branch --base origin/main --codex-bin .artifacts/codex-flex` (clean: no accepted/actionable findings)\n",
        "branch": "codex/skill-allowlist-merge",
